50 SECTION 3.
51 Said title is further amended in said article by revising Code Section 16-3-26, relating to
52 coercion, as follows:
53 "16-3-26.
54 A person is not guilty of a crime, except murder, if the act upon which the supposed
55 criminal liability is based is performed under such coercion that the person he or she
56 reasonably believes that performing the act is the only way necessary to prevent his
57 imminent death or great bodily injury to himself or herself or a third person."
