218 (e) The privilege created by this Code section shall not be grounds to fail to comply with
219 mandatory reporting requirements as set forth in Code Section 19-7-5 or Chapter 5 of
220 Title 30, the 'Disabled Adults and Elder Persons Protection Act.'
221 (f) No facilitator shall be held liable for civil damages for any statement, action, omission,
222 or decision made in the course of a victim centered practice or victim-offender dialogue
223 unless that statement, action, omission, or decision is:
224 (1) Grossly negligent and made with malice; or
225 (2) Made with willful disregard for the safety or property of any party to the victim
226 centered practice or victim-offender dialogue."
